transcription.text:
Speaker 1: Thank you for calling Viagra, how can I help you?

Speaker 2: Yes ma'am, I'd like to see about canceling my prescription.

Speaker 1: Okay, can I get the phone number that's associated with your account please?

Speaker 2: The what number?

Speaker 1: Your phone number.

Speaker 2: Oh, it's 903-275-8083.

Speaker 1: Okay, thank you Mr. Hendricks, I have your account pulled up.

Speaker 2: I see that you're a VIP status customer and have been for quite some time.

Speaker 1: And as a VIP customer you can always modify the frequency and quantity of your orders.

Speaker 2: Or put a pause on your account at any time.

Speaker 1: You're not required to be locked into automatic refills.

Speaker 2: Did you want me to put a hold on your account?

Speaker 1: And since you are a VIP, do you get special pricing as well as have access to your prescription?

Speaker 2: Well, I don't know, I'm starting to get a headache from it.

Speaker 1: Okay, well I'm glad you let me know that because you're a VIP customer,

Speaker 2: there's great perks that come with that, right?

Speaker 1: So I don't know if you've heard of the new AGV Viagra,

Speaker 2: but Pfizer recently made modifications and improvements to the Viagra.

Speaker 1: It's FDA approved, it's made in the same lab as the branded Viagra by the same manufacturer,

Speaker 2: and what they've done is they've actually altered some of the inactive ingredients

Speaker 1: so that the delivery mechanism makes it as such that it's eliminated those common side effects

Speaker 2: which people used to experience with the Viagra, which the most common one being headache.

Speaker 1: I can send you a sample of 10 to try, and then I can put your account on a hold until August 19th,

Speaker 2: that way you have an opportunity to try it out

Speaker 1: and then decide how you want to set up your account going forward.

Speaker 2: No, I think I just want to go ahead and cancel.

Speaker 1: Okay, you don't want to get 10 free AGV?

Speaker 2: I mean, they're in high demand because of how happy people are with it.

Speaker 1: Yeah, I've seen the things on it, but yeah, no, I'm good.

Speaker 2: I mean, there's no risk to you to try it out.

Speaker 1: I mean, you've been a customer for so long, might as well.

Speaker 2: Yeah, but I don't want to forget to call back if I don't like it or whatever,

Speaker 1: so I'd rather just go ahead and cancel.

Speaker 2: Okay, I mean, you have six months to think about it,

Speaker 1: and putting it on a hold is not going to put you back on the reoccurring every three months.

Speaker 2: I can give you my direct extension.

Speaker 1: If you wanted to extend that hold past six months, you could,

Speaker 2: or if you wanted to place an order before then or set up your account differently,

Speaker 1: you could also.

Speaker 2: Well, y'all do stuff more than that, right, Viagra, more than Viagra,

Speaker 1: or is that all y'all do?

Speaker 2: We have Cialis, too.

Speaker 1: See, I was going to say about trying that, and if it worked, then get back with y'all.

Speaker 2: Okay, well, we also have Cialis.

Speaker 1: We have the one you take daily and the one that you would take on an as-needed basis

Speaker 2: that lasts up to 72 hours.

Speaker 1: Right, right.

Speaker 2: Well, I want to make sure and find out first if it's going to work and stuff.

Speaker 1: Yeah, well, I mean, again, I could send you a sample of the Cialis if you wanted.

Speaker 2: Well, I want to go ahead and cancel first

Speaker 1: because I can get that at my doctor here just to see if it works.

Speaker 2: Okay.

Speaker 1: Well, once you cancel, like I said, it cancels your prescription from the doctor,

Speaker 2: and also you lose your VIP status.

Speaker 1: Okay, that's okay.

Speaker 2: Okay.

Speaker 1: Are you sure you don't want to try the AGV, Viagra?

Speaker 2: Are you sure you're turning something down that could be really great for you?

Speaker 1: No, I'm good.

Speaker 2: All right, sir, no problem.

Speaker 1: I've gone ahead and I've canceled you.

Speaker 2: Have a great day.

Speaker 1: You too.

Speaker 2: Thanks.
